76561198067888927,Not Recommended,248650,10157017,"Posted: 18 May, 2014",all,Epic Lad,"Overall-4/10Value for Price-Buying it on sale is a must. Considering there are free versions of the game on other platforms I am not sure why its normally valued at $5. I know five bucks is cheap, but the game really isnt worth more than a couple dollars in my opinion.Gameplay-Stickman felt like it was designed for either a younger or less experienced gamer. The Idea of drawing your own tools and items was the primary selling point for me. Unfortunatley, its actually just about 5 options the entire game- axe, key, cloud, fire, and armor. You cannot be creative and draw anything outside of that criteria.Sound-The music was fantastic and catchy. No complaints there. The main menu's music sounded oddly similar to the menu-tune from ""The Wolf Among Us"" by Telltale games.Graphics-The game delivers exactly what you would expect from a stick-figure title. however, the customization of your character was slightly dissapointing due to the bulky lines you had to doodle with. A fine-point pencil/pen would have been better in my opinion.Replay Value-The game was too short and the only challenging level was the final boss fight. I cant see myself replaying a game this quick and easy.I cant recommend this game to most customers. If you are purchasing for a younger person or new gamer it might be worth your time."
