76561198025604634,Recommended,248650,7922068,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,starkwolf,"Hard to put a yes/no on this one, butfor the priceof 2.99 I would say it's alright. This game is like a piece of candy: cheap, enjoyable, but don't expect it to last. Some levels were challenging, others not so much. The greatest pleasure in this game comes from the creative characters. Funny watching yourself get saved by your own dog, or a wierd creature trying to save a dalek. I also enjoy making very ""creative"" keys, axes, and other things. you can watch your character chop down about three targets with a stapler if you want, or make it look like an accessory while your character holds it. However, ""challenging"" puzzles weren't quite as fun since you are basically wandering around aimlessly if you can't figure out the next step. It can be painfully annoying, rather than tricky in the fun way. I think with a lot more options, both in crayon types and in world build, it might be more fun. Some (even the later levels and the Christmas one) are simple, and go by very fast. I have already beat a vast majority of the game in 8.5 hours, albeit I peaked at a few solutions after the ""challenge"" was no longer enjoyable. I would like to see a game with more strategy options, where if you are confused you are still trying things, rather than wandering around aimlessly."
